Southern Oasis hardening crews have requested practical support through the Midgaard postmaster's office to verify that their heat-surge casualty triage protocols function under actual Scorching Sands conditions. An ashglass survey slate documenting current thermal anomaly readings in the channel approaches must be recovered and returned so the hardening crews can calibrate their emergency response protocols for the coming transit season.
The ashglass survey slate has been recovered and its thermal readings forwarded to the Southern Oasis hardening crews through the Midgaard postmaster's office. The hardening crews have updated their heat-surge response calibration using the new anomaly data. The triage drill completion has been logged with the Southern Oasis Ration Dispatch as evidence that active-operator practical support protocols are functioning within acceptable response parameters.

